To the National Working Committee (NWC) of the All Progressives Congress (APC), the victory of former Lagos State Government Asiwaju Bola Ahmed Tinubu has attested to the ruling party’s nationalistic outlook. The attestation was contained in a congratulatory letter by party’s National Chairman, Senator Abdullahi Adamu on behalf of NWC to Tinubu on his victory at the presidential primary. Adamu said he was pleased with Tinubu’s triumph, that his emergence was a demonstration of his acceptance with the overwhelming vote that returned him as the party’s presidential candidate by the delegates.   Tinubu: The triumph of hope     Buhari pledges full support for Tinubu     Firm bags Shell’s Leadership awards   The message reads: “I present to Your Excellency, Senator Bola Ahmed Tinubu, my compliments and those of the members of the NWC of the APC, in the best of traditions. “I write on behalf of the entire membership of the All Progressives Congress to congratulate Your Excellency on the sterling victory that you recorded at the just concluded Special National Convention to emerge as the Presidential Candidate of our great party. “It is my sincere hope and prayer that our collaborative efforts between the Party’s National Secretariat and your Presidential campaign team will proceed with the shared expectations of victory at the 2023 general elections, by the grace of God.”